{{Infobox philosopher | image = Antoine Blanc de Saint-Bonnet.jpg | caption = Bust of Antoine Blanc de Saint-Bonnet. | name = Blanc de Saint-Bonnet | birth_name = Antoine-Joseph-Elisée-Adolphe Blanc de Saint-Bonnet | birth_date = {{birth date|df=y|1815|1|28}} | birth_place = [[Lyon]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=y|1880|6|8|1815|1|28}} | death_place = [[Lyon]] | nationality = French | school_tradition = [[Ultramontanism]], [[Royalism]] | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | influences = | influenced = | notable_ideas = | signature = }} '''Antoine Blanc de Saint-Bonnet''' (28 January 1815 &ndash; 2 June 1880) was a French philosopher,<ref>Beum, Robert (1997). [http://www.mmisi.org/ma/39_03/beum.pdf "Ultra-Royalism Revisited: An Annotated Bibliography,"] ''Modern Age,'' Vol. 39, No. 3, p. 302.</ref> whose ideas were a precursor to modern sociology.
